In this article, President Trump discusses the outcomes of his recent 12-day trip to Asia. He highlights the hospitality and respect the American delegation received and the deals that were made, which could potentially create jobs in the US. Trump also mentions the renegotiation of trade deals and the need for fair treatment in trade. He then announces that the United States is designating North Korea as a state sponsor of terrorism, imposing further sanctions on the country. The article also touches on domestic policy issues, such as the passing of a tax cut by the House of Representatives and the hope for Senate approval. Trump emphasizes the relief the tax plan will bring to hardworking families and the goal of bringing jobs back to the US. The article concludes with mentions of reducing government spending, plans for healthcare, infrastructure, and welfare reform, and addressing the opioid epidemic. Trump also extends Thanksgiving wishes and discusses the need for border security.